of locations affected by the <a href="/wiki/Severe_acute_respiratory_syndrome_coronavirus_2" title="Severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2">severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2</a> (SARS-CoV-2), the virus which causes <a href="/wiki/Coronavirus_disease_2019" title="Coronavirus disease 2019">coronavirus disease 2019</a> (COVID-19) and is responsible for the <a href="/wiki/COVID-19_pandemic" title="COVID-19 pandemic">COVID-19 pandemic</a>. The first human cases of COVID-19 were identified in <a href="/wiki/Wuhan" title="Wuhan">Wuhan</a> the capital of the province of <a href="/wiki/Hubei" title="Hubei">Hubei</a> in <a href="/wiki/China" title="China">China</a> in December 2019. The most recent country or territory to report its first confirmed case was <a href="/wiki/COVID-19_pandemic_in_Antarctica" title="COVID-19 pandemic in Antarctica">Antarctica</a> on 21 December 2020.\n</p>\n<style data-mw-deduplicate="TemplateStyles:r886046785">.mw-parser-output .toclimit-2 .toclevel-1 ul,.mw-parser-output .toclimit-3 .toclevel-2 ul,.mw-parser-output .toclimit-4 .toclevel-3 confirmed cases, 35,145,678 active cases, 47,562,641 recoveries, and 1,835,113 deaths in about 191 countries/territories<sup id="cite_ref-JHU_ticker_4-5" class="reference"><a title="Coordinated Universal Time">UTC</a>) \xc2\xb7 History of <a href="/wiki/COVID-19_pandemic_cases" title="COVID-19 pandemic cases">cases</a> \xc2\xb7 History of <a href="/wiki/COVID-19_pandemic_deaths" title="COVID-19 pandemic deaths">deaths</a>\n</td></tr>\n<tr style="text-align:left;" class="sortbottom">\n<td colspan="6" style="width:1px;"><b>Notes</b><div style="font-size: 111.111%;"><div class="reflist" style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;">\n<div class="mw-references-wrap mw-references-columns"><ol class="references">\n<li id="cite_note-8"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-8">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><b>Location:</b> Countries, territories, and international conveyances where cases were diagnosed. The nationality of the infected and the origin of infection may vary. For some countries, cases are split into respective territories and noted accordingly.</span>\n</li>\n<li id="cite_note-ccc-10"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-ccc_10-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><b>Cases:</b> This number shows the cumulative number of confirmed human cases reported to date. The actual number of infections and cases is likely to be higher than reported.<sup id="cite_ref-9" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-9">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup> Reporting criteria and <a href="/wiki/COVID-19_testing" title="COVID-19 testing">testing capacity</a> vary between locations.</span>\n</li>\n<li id="cite_note-11"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-11">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><b>Deaths:</b> Reporting criteria vary between locations.</span>\n</li>\n<li id="cite_note-12"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-12">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><b>Recoveries:</b> May not correspond to actual current figures and not all recoveries may be reported. Reporting criteria vary between locations and some countries do not report recoveries.</span>\n</li>\n<li id="cite_note-13"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-13">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">The worldwide totals for cases, deaths and recoveries are taken from the Johns Hopkins University Coronavirus Resource Center. They are not sums of the figures for the listed countries and territories.</span>\n</li>\n<li id="cite_note-20"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-20">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><b>United States</b><div><ol style="list-style-type:decimal"><li>Figures include cases identified on the <a href="/wiki/COVID-19_pandemic_on_cruise_ships#Grand_Princess" title="COVID-19 pandemic on cruise ships"><i>Grand Princess</i></a>.</li><li>Figures do not include the <a href="/wiki/Unincorporated_territories_of_the_United_States" title="Unincorporated territories of the United States">unincorporated territories</a> of <a href="/wiki/COVID-19_pandemic_in_Puerto_Rico" title="COVID-19 pandemic in Puerto Rico">Puerto Rico</a>, <a href="/wiki/COVID-19_pandemic_in_Guam" title="COVID-19 pandemic in Guam">Guam</a>, <a href="/wiki/COVID-19_pandemic_in_the_Northern_Mariana_Islands" title="COVID-19 pandemic in the Northern Mariana Islands">Northern Marian Islands</a>, and <a href="/wiki/COVID-19_pandemic_in_the_United_States_Virgin_Islands" title="COVID-19 pandemic in the United States Virgin Islands">U.S Virgin Islands</a>, all of which are listed separately.</li><li>Not all states or overseas territories report recovery data.</li><li>Cases include clinically diagnosed cases as per CDC guidelines.<sup id="cite_ref-14" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-14">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup></li><li>Recoveries and deaths include probable deaths and people released from quarantine as per CDC guidelines.<sup id="cite_ref-15" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-15">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-16" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-16">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-17" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-17">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup></li><li>Figures from the <a href="/wiki/United_States_Department_of_Defense" title="United States Department of Defense">United States Department of Defense</a> are only released on a branch-by branch basis since April 2020, without distinction between domestic and foreign deployment, and cases may be reported to local health authorities.<sup id="cite_ref-DoD_stop_18-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-DoD_stop-18">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup></li><li>Cases for the <a href="/wiki/COVID-19_pandemic_on_USS_Theodore_Roosevelt" title="COVID-19 pandemic on USS Theodore Roosevelt">USS <i>Theodore Roosevelt</i></a>, currently docked at Guam, are reported separate from national figures but included in the Navy\'s totals.</li><li>There is also one case reported from <a href="/wiki/Guantanamo_Bay_Naval_Base" title="Guantanamo Bay Naval Base">Guantanamo Bay Naval Base</a> not included in any other nation or territory\'s counts.<sup id="cite_ref-19" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-19">&#91;14&#93;</a></sup> Since April 2020, the <a href="/wiki/United_States_Department_of_Defense" title="United States Department of Defense">United States Department of Defense</a> has directed all bases, including Guantanamo Bay, to not publish case statistics.<sup id="cite_ref-DoD_stop_18-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-DoD_stop-18">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup></li></ol></div></span>\n</li>\n<li id="cite_note-25"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-25">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><b>Russia</b><div><ol style="list-style-type:decimal"><li>Including cases from the <a href="/wiki/Political_status_of_Crimea" title="Political status of Crimea">disputed</a> <a href="/wiki/COVID-19_pandemic_in_Crimea" title="COVID-19 pandemic in Crimea">Crimea</a> and <a href="/wiki/COVID-19_pandemic_in_Sevastopol" title="COVID-19 pandemic in Sevastopol">Sevastopol</a>.</li><li>Excluding cases from the <i><a href="/wiki/COVID-19_pandemic_on_Diamond_Princess" title="COVID-19 pandemic on Diamond Princess">Diamond Princess</a></i> cruise ship, which are classified as "on an international conveyance".</li></ol></div></span>\n</li>\n<li id="cite_note-28"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-28">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><b>France</b><div><ol style="list-style-type:decimal"><li>Including <a href="/wiki/Overseas_department_and_region" class="mw-redirect" title="Overseas department and country</span></h3>\n<p>This table contains the cumulative number of monthly deaths from <a href="/wiki/COVID-19_pandemic" title="COVID-19 pandemic">the pandemic</a> of <a title="World Health Organization">World Health Organization</a> (WHO) and published in the WHO\'s daily situation reports.\n</p>\n<link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" world.</div></div></div></div>\n<div style="clear:both;"></div>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="By_continent">By continent</span></h2>\n<div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable">Further information: <a href="/wiki/National_responses_to_the_COVID-19_pandemic" title="National responses to the COVID-19 pandemic">National responses to the COVID-19 pandemic</a></div>\n<p>As a result of COVID-19 many regions have imposed  <a href="/wiki/COVID-19_pandemic_lockdowns" title="COVID-19 pandemic lockdowns">lockdowns, curfews and quarantines</a> alongside <a href="/wiki/List_of_COVID-19_pandemic_legislation" title="List of COVID-19 pandemic legislation">new legislation</a> and <a href="/wiki/Evacuations_related_to_the_COVID-19_pandemic" title="Evacuations related to the COVID-19 pandemic">evacuations</a>, or other restrictions for citizens of or recent travelers to the most affected areas.<sup id="cite_ref-419" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-419">&#91;362&#93;</a></sup> Other regions have imposed global restrictions that apply to all foreign countries and territories, or <a href="/wiki/Travel_restrictions_related_to_the_COVID-19_pandemic" title="Travel restrictions related to the COVID-19 pandemic">prevent their own citizens from travelling overseas</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-420" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-420">&#91;363&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Africa">Africa</span></h3>\n<div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable">Main article: <a href="/wiki/COVID-19_pandemic_in_Africa" title="COVID-19 pandemic in Africa">COVID-19 pandemic in Africa</a></div>\n<div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable">See also: <a href="/wiki/National_responses_to_the_COVID-19_pandemic_in_Africa" title="National responses to the COVID-19 pandemic in Africa">National responses to the COVID-19 pandemic in Africa</a></div>\n<div class="thumb tright"><div class="thumbinner" style="width:262px;"><a href="/wiki/File:COVID-19_Outbreak_Africa_Map.svg" class="image"><img alt="" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c6/COVID-19_Outbreak_Africa_Map.svg/260px-COVID-19_Outbreak_Africa_Map.svg.png" decoding="async" width="260" height="260" class="thumbimage" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c6/COVID-19_Outbreak_Africa_Map.svg/390px-COVID-19_Outbreak_Africa_Map.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c6/COVID-19_Outbreak_Africa_Map.svg/520px-COVID-19_Outbreak_Africa_Map.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="1000" data-file-height="1000" /></a>  <div class="thumbcaption"><div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:COVID-19_Outbreak_Africa_Map.svg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r981673959"/><div class="legend"><span class="legend-color" style="background-color:#ffC0C0; color:black; -webkit-column-break-inside: avoid;">&#160;</span>&#160;1\xe2\x80\x9399 confirmed cases</div> <link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r981673959"/><div class="legend"><span class="legend-color" style="background-color:#ee7070; color:black; -webkit-column-break-inside: avoid;">&#160;</span>&#160;100\xe2\x80\x93999 confirmed cases</div> <link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r981673959"/><div class="legend"><span class="legend-color" style="background-color:#c80200; color:white; -webkit-column-break-inside: avoid;">&#160;</span>&#160;1,000\xe2\x80\x939,999 confirmed cases</div> <link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r981673959"/><div class="legend"><span class="legend-color" style="background-color:#900000; color:white; -webkit-column-break-inside: avoid;">&#160;</span>&#160;10,000\xe2\x80\x9399,999 confirmed cases</div> <link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r981673959"/><div class="legend"><span class="legend-color" style="background-color:#510000; color:white; -webkit-column-break-inside: avoid;">&#160;</span>&#160;100,000+ confirmed cases</div></div></div></div>\n<div class="excerpt-block"><style data-mw-deduplicate="TemplateStyles:r952607947">.mw-parser-output .excerpt .selflink{font-weight:normal}.mw-parser-output .excerpt-indicator{border-left:3px solid #c8ccd1;margin:1em 0;padding-left:1em}</style><div class="excerpt">\n<p>The pandemic was confirmed to have spread to Africa on 14 February 2020, with the first confirmed case announced in <a href="/wiki/COVID-19_pandemic_in_Egypt" title="COVID-19 pandemic in Egypt">Egypt</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-421" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-421">&#91;364&#93;</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-422" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-422">&#91;365&#93;</a></sup> The first confirmed case in <a href="/wiki/Sub-Saharan_Africa" title="Sub-Saharan Africa">sub-Saharan Africa</a> was announced in <a href="/wiki/COVID-19_pandemic_in_Nigeria" title="COVID-19 pandemic in Nigeria">Nigeria</a> at the end of February.<sup id="cite_ref-423" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-423">&#91;366&#93;</a></sup> Within three months, the virus had spread throughout the continent, as <a href="/wiki/Lesotho" title="Lesotho">Lesotho</a>, the last African sovereign state to have remained free of the virus, reported a case on 13 May.<sup id="cite_ref-424" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-424">&#91;367&#93;</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-COVID-19_pandemic_in_Africa_latimes.com_425-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-COVID-19_pandemic_in_Africa_latimes.com-425">&#91;368&#93;</a></sup> By 26 May, it appeared that most African countries were experiencing community transmission, although testing capacity was limited.<sup id="cite_ref-426" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-426">&#91;369&#93;</a></sup> Most of the identified imported cases arrived from <a href="/wiki/Europe" title="Europe">Europe</a> and the <a href="/wiki/United_States" title="United States">United States</a> rather than from <a href="/wiki/China" title="China">China</a> where the virus originated.<sup id="cite_ref-COVID-19_pandemic_in_Africa_Africa_Braces_427-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-COVID-19_pandemic_in_Africa_Africa_Braces-427">&#91;370&#93;</a></sup> It is believed that there is widespread <a href="/wiki/Under-reporting" title="Under-reporting">under-reporting</a> in many African countries with less developed <a href="/wiki/Healthcare_system" class="mw-redirect" title="Healthcare system">healthcare systems</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-428" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-428">&#91;371&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\nExperts have worried about <a href="/wiki/COVID-19" class="mw-redirect" title="COVID-19">COVID-19</a> spreading to Africa, because many of the <a href="/wiki/Healthcare_systems" class="mw-redirect" title="Healthcare systems">healthcare systems</a> on the continent are inadequate, having problems such as lack of equipment, lack of funding, insufficient training of healthcare workers, and inefficient data transmission. It was feared that the pandemic could be difficult to keep under control in Africa, and could cause huge economic problems if it spread widely.<sup id="cite_ref-COVID-19_pandemic_in_Africa_African_Countries_Respond_Quickly_429-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-COVID-19_pandemic_in_Africa_African_Countries_Respond_Quickly-429">&#91;372&#93;</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-COVID-19_pandemic_in_Africa_Africa_Braces_427-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-COVID-19_pandemic_in_Africa_Africa_Braces-427">&#91;370&#93;</a></sup> As of 18 April 2020, the supply of <a href="/wiki/Ventilator" title="Ventilator">ventilators</a> was low in much of Africa: 41 countries had only 2,000 ventilators between them, and ten countries had no ventilators at all. Even basic supplies like soap and water are subject to shortages in parts of the continent.<sup id="cite_ref-430" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-430">&#91;373&#93;</a></sup></div></div>\n<div style="clear:both;"></div>\n<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Antarctica">Antarctica</span></h3>\n<div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable">Main article: <a href="/wiki/COVID-19_pandemic_in_Antarctica" title="COVID-19 pandemic in Antarctica">COVID-19 pandemic in Antarctica</a></div>\n<p>The first cases of <a href="/wiki/COVID-19_pandemic_in_Antarctica" title="COVID-19 pandemic in Antarctica">COVID-19 in Antarctica</a> were reported by Chile on 21 December 2020. 36 people, 10 maintenance workers and 26 officers, contracted the virus in the <a href="/wiki/Base_General_Bernardo_O%27Higgins" class="mw-redirect" title="Base General Bernardo O&#39;Higgins">Base General Bernardo O\'Higgins</a>, a Chilean research base situated in the <a href="/wiki/Trinity_Peninsula" title="Trinity Peninsula">Trinity Peninsula</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-431" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-431">&#91;374&#93;</a></sup> With these cases, the COVID-19 pandemic has officially spread to every continent in the world.<sup id="cite_ref-432" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-432">&#91;375&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Asia">Asia</span></h3>\n<div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable">Main article: <a href="/wiki/COVID-19_pandemic_in_Asia" title="COVID-19 pandemic in Asia">COVID-19 pandemic in Asia</a></div>\n<div class="thumb tright"><div class="thumbinner" style="width:262px;"><a href="/wiki/File:COVID-19_deaths_per_million_residents_as_of_December_10,_2020.svg" class="image"><img alt="" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r952607947"/><div class="excerpt">\n<p>The <a href="/wiki/COVID-19_pandemic" title="COVID-19 pandemic">COVID-19 pandemic</a> began in <a href="/wiki/Asia" title="Asia">Asia</a> in <a href="/wiki/Wuhan" title="Wuhan">Wuhan</a>, <a href="/wiki/Hubei" title="Hubei">Hubei</a>, China, and has spread widely through the continent. As of 30&#160;April&#160;2020<sup class="plainlinks noexcerpt noprint asof-tag update" style="display:none;"><a class="external text" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=COVID-19_pandemic_by_country_and_territory&amp;action=edit">&#91;update&#93;</a></sup>,<sup id="cite_ref-COVID-19_pandemic_in_Asia_Taj1st_433-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-COVID-19_pandemic_in_Asia_Taj1st-433">&#91;376&#93;</a></sup> at least one case of COVID-19 had been reported in every country in Asia except <a href="/wiki/North_Korea" title="North Korea">North Korea</a> and <a href="/wiki/Turkmenistan" title="Turkmenistan">Turkmenistan</a>.\n</p>\nAsian countries with the highest numbers of confirmed coronavirus cases are <a href="/wiki/COVID-19_pandemic_in_India" title="COVID-19 pandemic in India">India</a>, <a href="/wiki/COVID-19_pandemic_in_Russia" title="COVID-19 pandemic in Russia">Russia</a> (a <a href="/wiki/Transcontinental" class="mw-disambig" title="Transcontinental">transcontinental</a> country),  <a href="/wiki/COVID-19_pandemic_in_Turkey" title="COVID-19 pandemic in Turkey">Turkey</a>, <a href="/wiki/COVID-19_pandemic_in_Iran" title="COVID-19 pandemic in Iran">Iran</a>,  and <a href="/wiki/COVID-19_pandemic_in_Indonesia" title="COVID-19 pandemic in Indonesia">Indonesia</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-434" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-434">&#91;377&#93;</a></sup> Among the earliest countries to report COVID-19 cases after the outbreak in <a href="/wiki/COVID-19_pandemic_in_mainland_China" title="COVID-19 pandemic in mainland China">China</a> were <a href="/wiki/COVID-19_pandemic_in_Thailand" title="COVID-19 pandemic in Thailand">Thailand</a>, <a href="/wiki/COVID-19_pandemic_in_Japan" title="COVID-19 pandemic in Japan">Japan</a>, <a href="/wiki/COVID-19_pandemic_in_South_Korea" title="COVID-19 pandemic in South Korea">South Korea</a>, <a href="/wiki/COVID-19_pandemic_in_Taiwan" title="COVID-19 pandemic in Taiwan">Taiwan</a>, and <a href="/wiki/COVID-19_pandemic_in_Vietnam" title="COVID-19 pandemic in Vietnam">Vietnam</a>, but these countries had successfully controlled the pandemic. The highest numbers of deaths are recorded in India, Iran, Indonesia, Turkey and Iraq with more than 240,000 deaths combined.  The death tolls in a number of countries, however, are claimed to be significantly higher than those given in official figures.<sup id="cite_ref-435" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-435">&#91;378&#93;</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-436" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-436">&#91;379&#93;</a></sup></div></div>\n<div style="clear:both;"></div>\n<h3><span text" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=COVID-19_pandemic_by_country_and_territory&amp;action=edit">&#91;update&#93;</a></sup> when the number of new cases became greater  than those in China, the <a href="/wiki/World_Health_Organization" title="World Health Organization">World Health Organization</a> (WHO) began to consider Europe the active centre of the <a href="/wiki/COVID-19_pandemic" title="COVID-19 pandemic">pandemic</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-COVID-19_pandemic_in_Europe_Centre_437-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-COVID-19_pandemic_in_Europe_Centre-437">&#91;380&#93;</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-438" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-438">&#91;381&#93;</a></sup> Cases by country across Europe had doubled over periods of typically 3 to 4 days, with some countries (mostly those at earlier stages of detection) showing doubling every 2 days.<sup id="cite_ref-439" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-439">&#91;382&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\nAs of 17 March,<sup class="plainlinks noexcerpt noprint asof-tag update" style="display:none;"><a class="external text" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=COVID-19_pandemic_by_country_and_territory&amp;action=edit">&#91;update&#93;</a></sup> all countries within Europe had a confirmed case of <a href="/wiki/Coronavirus_disease_2019" title="Coronavirus disease 2019">COVID-19</a>, with <a href="/wiki/Montenegro" title="Montenegro">Montenegro</a> being the last European country to report at least one case.<sup id="cite_ref-440" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-440">&#91;383&#93;</a></sup> At least one death has been reported in all European countries, apart from the <a href="/wiki/Vatican_City" title="Vatican City">Vatican City</a>.</div></div>\n<div style="clear:both;"></div>\n<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="North_America">North America</span></h3>\n<div rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r952607947"/><div class="excerpt">\n<p>The first cases in North America were reported in the <a href="/wiki/COVID-19_pandemic_in_the_United_States" title="COVID-19 pandemic in the United States">United States</a> in January 2020. Cases were reported in all North American countries after <a href="/wiki/COVID-19_pandemic_in_Saint_Kitts_and_Nevis" title="COVID-19 pandemic in Saint Kitts and Nevis">Saint Kitts and Nevis</a> confirmed a case on 25 March, and in all North American territories after <a href="/wiki/COVID-19_pandemic_in_Bonaire" title="COVID-19 pandemic in Bonaire">Bonaire</a> confirmed a case on 16 April.<sup id="cite_ref-COVID-19_pandemic_in_North_America_FirstBonaire_local_441-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-COVID-19_pandemic_in_North_America_FirstBonaire_local-441">&#91;384&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>On 26 March 2020, the U.S. became the country with the highest number of confirmed COVID-19 infections, with over 82,000 cases.<sup id="cite_ref-442" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-442">&#91;385&#93;</a></sup> On 11 April 2020, the U.S. became the country with the highest official death toll for COVID-19, with over 20,000 deaths.<sup id="cite_ref-443" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-443">&#91;386&#93;</a></sup> As of 21 November 2020 the total cases of COVID-19 are over 13,942,964 with over 383,084 total deaths.<sup id="cite_ref-444" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-444">&#91;387&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<a href="/wiki/COVID-19_pandemic_in_Canada" title="COVID-19 pandemic in Canada">Canada</a> reported 117,658 cases and 3,842 deaths on 30 July, while <a href="/wiki/COVID-19_pandemic_in_Mexico" title="COVID-19 pandemic in Mexico">Mexico</a> reported 416,179 cases and 46,000 deaths.<sup id="cite_ref-445" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-445">&#91;388&#93;</a></sup> The most cases by state is Texas with about 17,279 deaths and over 849,000 confirmed cases.</div></div>\n<div style="clear:both;"></div>\n<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Oceania">Oceania</span></h3>\n<div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable">Main article: <a <div class="thumbcaption"><div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:COVID-19_Outbreak_Cases_in_Oceania.svg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" style="background-color:#ee7070; color:black; -webkit-column-break-inside: avoid;">&#160;</span>&#160;10\xe2\x80\x9399 confirmed cases</div> <link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r981673959"/><div class="legend"><span class="legend-color" style="background-color:#c80200; color:white; -webkit-column-break-inside: avoid;">&#160;</span>&#160;100\xe2\x80\x93999 confirmed cases</div> <link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r981673959"/><div class="legend"><span class="legend-color" style="background-color:#900000; color:white; -webkit-column-break-inside: avoid;">&#160;</span>&#160;1000\xe2\x80\x939999 confirmed cases</div> <link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r981673959"/><div class="legend"><span class="legend-color" style="background-color:#510000; color:white; -webkit-column-break-inside: avoid;">&#160;</span>&#160;10,000+ confirmed cases</div></div></div></div>\n<div class="excerpt-block"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r952607947"/><div class="excerpt">\nThe <a href="/wiki/COVID-19_pandemic" title="COVID-19 pandemic">pandemic</a> was confirmed to have reached <a href="/wiki/Oceania" title="Oceania">Oceania</a> on 25 January 2020 with the first confirmed case reported in <a href="/wiki/Melbourne" title="Melbourne">Melbourne</a>, <a href="/wiki/Victoria_(Australia)" title="Victoria (Australia)">Victoria</a>, <a href="/wiki/COVID-19_pandemic_in_Australia" title="COVID-19 pandemic in Australia">Australia</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-COVID-19_pandemic_in_Oceania_AustraliaCase1_446-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-COVID-19_pandemic_in_Oceania_AustraliaCase1-446">&#91;389&#93;</a></sup> It has since spread elsewhere in the region,<sup id="cite_ref-COVID-19_pandemic_in_Oceania_WHO_Dashboard_447-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-COVID-19_pandemic_in_Oceania_WHO_Dashboard-447">&#91;390&#93;</a></sup> although many small Pacific <a href="/wiki/Island_country" title="Island country">island nations</a> have thus far avoided the outbreak by closing their international borders. Six Oceania sovereign states have yet to report a case: <a href="/wiki/Kiribati" title="Kiribati">Kiribati</a>, the <a href="/wiki/Federated_States_of_Micronesia" title="Federated States of Micronesia">Federated States of Micronesia</a>, <a href="/wiki/Nauru" title="Nauru">Nauru</a>, <a href="/wiki/Palau" title="Palau">Palau</a>, <a href="/wiki/Tonga" title="Tonga">Tonga</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Tuvalu" title="Tuvalu">Tuvalu</a>. Australia and <a href="/wiki/COVID-19_pandemic_in_New_Zealand" title="COVID-19 pandemic in New Zealand">New Zealand</a> have been praised for their handling of the pandemic compared to other western nations, with the latter wiping out all community transmission of the virus. The most recent country or territory to report its first confirmed case was <a href="/wiki/Samoa" title="Samoa">Samoa</a>, on 18 November 2020.</div></div>\n<div style="clear:both;"></div>\n<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="South_America">South America</span></h3>\n<div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable">Main article: <a href="/wiki/COVID-19_pandemic_in_South_America" title="COVID-19 pandemic in South America">COVID-19 pandemic in South America</a></div>\n<div class="thumb tright"><div class="thumbinner" style="width:262px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Map_of_coronavirus_cases_in_Latin_America_by_second-level_administrative_division.png" class="image"><img alt="" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/18/Map_of_coronavirus_cases_in_Latin_America_by_second-level_administrative_division.png/260px-Map_of_coronavirus_cases_in_Latin_America_by_second-level_administrative_division.png" decoding="async" width="260" height="277" class="thumbimage" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/18/Map_of_coronavirus_cases_in_Latin_America_by_second-level_administrative_division.png/390px-Map_of_coronavirus_cases_in_Latin_America_by_second-level_administrative_division.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/18/Map_of_coronavirus_cases_in_Latin_America_by_second-level_administrative_division.png/520px-Map_of_coronavirus_cases_in_Latin_America_by_second-level_administrative_division.png 2x" data-file-width="7000" data-file-height="7456" /></a>  <div class="thumbcaption"><div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Map_of_coronavirus_cases_in_Latin_America_by_second-level_administrative_division.png" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r981673959"/><div class="legend"><span class="legend-color" style="background-color:#fee5d9; color:black; -webkit-column-break-inside: avoid;">&#160;</span>&#160;no confirmed cases</div> <link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r981673959"/><div class="legend"><span class="legend-color" style="background-color:#fcbba1; color:black; -webkit-column-break-inside: avoid;">&#160;</span>&#160;1\xe2\x80\x9349 confirmed cases</div> <link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r981673959"/><div class="legend"><span class="legend-color" style="background-color:#fb6a4a; color:black; -webkit-column-break-inside: avoid;">&#160;</span>&#160;50\xe2\x80\x9399 confirmed cases</div> <link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r981673959"/><div class="legend"><span class="legend-color" style="background-color:#de2d26; color:white; -webkit-column-break-inside: avoid;">&#160;</span>&#160;100\xe2\x80\x93249 confirmed cases</div> <link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r981673959"/><div class="legend"><span class="legend-color" style="background-color:#a50f15; color:white; -webkit-column-break-inside: avoid;">&#160;</span>&#160;250\xe2\x80\x93499 confirmed cases</div> <link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r981673959"/><div class="legend"><span class="legend-color" style="background-color:#630606; color:white; -webkit-column-break-inside: avoid;">&#160;</span>&#160;500\xe2\x80\x93999 confirmed cases</div> <link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r981673959"/><div class="legend"><span class="legend-color" style="background-color:#3a0303; color:white; -webkit-column-break-inside: avoid;">&#160;</span>&#160;1000+ confirmed cases</div></div></div></div>\n<div class="excerpt-block"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r952607947"/><div class="excerpt">\n<p>The pandemic was confirmed to have reached <a href="/wiki/South_America" title="South America">South America</a> on 26 February 2020 when <a href="/wiki/Brazil" title="Brazil">Brazil</a> confirmed a case in <a href="/wiki/S%C3%A3o_Paulo" title="S\xc3\xa3o Paulo">S\xc3\xa3o Paulo</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-448" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-448">&#91;391&#93;</a></sup> By 3 April, all countries and territories in South America had recorded at least one case.<sup id="cite_ref-Stuff/Fairfax_449-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Stuff/Fairfax-449">&#91;392&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>On 13 May, it was reported that Latin America and the <a href="/wiki/Caribbean" title="Caribbean">Caribbean</a> had reported over 400,000 cases of infection with 23,091 deaths. On 22 May, citing especially the rapid increase of infections <a href="/wiki/COVID-19_pandemic_in_Brazil" title="COVID-19 pandemic in Brazil">in Brazil</a>, the WHO declared South America the epicentre of the pandemic.<sup id="cite_ref-450" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-450">&#91;393&#93;</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-451" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-451">&#91;394&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\nAs of 20 September,<sup class="noprint Inline-Template" style="white-space:nowrap;">&#91;<i><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Manual_of_Style/Dates_and_numbers#Chronological_items" title="Wikipedia:Manual of Style/Dates and numbers"><span title="The date of the event predicted near this tag has passed. (November 2020)">needs update</span></a></i>&#93;</sup> South America has about 7.5 million confirmed cases and 238,000 deaths. Due to a dearth of testing and medical facilities, it is believed that the outbreak is far larger than the official numbers show.<sup id="cite_ref-452" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-452">&#91;395&#93;</a></sup></div></div>\n<div style="clear:both;"></div>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="At_sea">At sea</span></h2>\n<div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable">Main articles: <a href="/wiki/COVID-19_pandemic_on_cruise_ships" title="COVID-19 pandemic on cruise ships">COVID-19 pandemic on cruise ships</a> and <a href="/wiki/COVID-19_pandemic_on_naval_ships" title="COVID-19 pandemic on naval ships">COVID-19 pandemic on naval ships</a></div>\n<div class="thumb tright"><div class="thumbinner" style="width:222px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Aerial_view_of_Diamond_Princess_with_Yokohama_City.jpg" class="image"><img alt="" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/ae/Aerial_view_of_Diamond_Princess_with_Yokohama_City.jpg/220px-Aerial_view_of_Diamond_Princess_with_Yokohama_City.jpg" decoding="async" width="220" height="165" class="thumbimage" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/ae/Aerial_view_of_Diamond_Princess_with_Yokohama_City.jpg/330px-Aerial_view_of_Diamond_Princess_with_Yokohama_City.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/ae/Aerial_view_of_Diamond_Princess_with_Yokohama_City.jpg/440px-Aerial_view_of_Diamond_Princess_with_Yokohama_City.jpg 2x" data-file-width="1784" data-file-height="1338" /></a>  <div class="thumbcaption"><div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Aerial_view_of_Diamond_Princess_with_Yokohama_City.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div><i><a href="/wiki/Diamond_Princess_(ship)" title="Diamond Princess (ship)">Diamond Princess</a></i> undergoing a cleaning and disinfection process at Daikoku Pier in <a href="/wiki/Yokohama_Port" class="mw-redirect" title="Yokohama Port">Yokohama Port</a> photographed on 1 March 2020</div></div></div>\n<div class="excerpt-block"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r952607947"/><div class="excerpt">\n<p>The <a href="/wiki/COVID-19_pandemic" title="COVID-19 pandemic">COVID-19 pandemic</a> spread to a number of <a href="/wiki/Cruise_ship" title="Cruise ship">cruise ships</a>, with the nature of such ships\xe2\x80\x94including crowded semi-enclosed areas, increased exposure to new environments, and limited medical resources\xe2\x80\x94contributing to the heightened risk and rapid spread of the disease.<sup id="cite_ref-453" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-453">&#91;396&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\nThe British-registered <a href="/wiki/Diamond_Princess_(ship)" title="Diamond Princess (ship)"><i>Diamond Princess</i></a> was the first cruise ship to have a major outbreak on board, with the ship <a href="/wiki/Quarantine" title="Quarantine">quarantined</a> at <a href="/wiki/Port_of_Yokohama" title="Port of Yokohama">Yokohama</a> from 4 February 2020 for approximately one month.  Over 700 people <a href="/wiki/COVID-19_pandemic_on_Diamond_Princess" title="COVID-19 pandemic on Diamond Princess">became infected</a>, and 14 people died. At the time, the ship accounted for over half the reported cases of <a href="/wiki/Severe_acute_respiratory_syndrome_coronavirus_2" title="Severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2">SARS-CoV-2</a> outside of mainland <a href="/wiki/China" title="China">China</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-COVID-19_pandemic_on_cruise_ships_theguardian1_454-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-COVID-19_pandemic_on_cruise_ships_theguardian1-454">&#91;397&#93;</a></sup></div></div>\n<div class="excerpt-block"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r952607947"/><div class="excerpt">\n<p>The <a href="/wiki/COVID-19_pandemic" title="COVID-19 pandemic">COVID-19 pandemic</a> spread to many military ships. The nature of these ships, which includes working with others in small enclosed areas and a lack of private quarters for the vast majority of crew, contributed to the rapid spread of the disease, even more so than on <a href="/wiki/COVID-19_pandemic_on_cruise_ships" title="COVID-19 pandemic on cruise ships">cruise ships</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-455" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-455">&#91;398&#93;</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-456" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-456">&#91;399&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\nDue to the nature of <a href="/wiki/Operations_security" title="Operations security">operations security</a>, national militaries may have policies in place that prevent or restrict reporting of SARS-CoV-2 infections and COVID-19 deaths, so although the cases listed below may have been widely reported in reliable sources, confirmation by official spokespeople of the respective militaries is not systematic.<sup id="cite_ref-457" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-457">&#91;400&#93;</a></sup></div></div>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Timeline_of_first_confirmed_case_by_country">Timeline of first confirmed case by # Convert source.content to a beautifulsoup object 
# beautifulsoup can parse (extract specific information) HTML code

soup = bs.BeautifulSoup(source.content, features='html.parser') 
# we pass in the source content
# features specifies what type of code we are parsing, 
# here 'html.parser' specifies that we want beautiful soup to parse HTML code
In [ ]:
country = list()
cases =  list()
deaths = list()
recoveries = list()

for countryinstance in soup.find(id="covid-19-pandemic-data").text.split("World[e]")[1].split('\n\n\n')[1:-4]:
    #print(countryinstance.split("\n")[0])
    country.append(countryinstance.split('\n\n')[1])
    cases.append(countryinstance.split('\n\n')[2])
    deaths.append(countryinstance.split('\n\n')[3])
    recoveries.append(countryinstance.split('\n\n')[4])
In [ ]:
In [ ]:
data  = {'Country': country,'Cases':cases,'Deaths':deaths,'Recoveries':recoveries}
#df.style.set_caption("Hello World")
data = pd.DataFrame(data)
In [ ]:
data['Cases'] =  pd.to_numeric(data['Cases'].str.replace('\W', ''),errors='coerce').fillna(0).astype(int)
data['Deaths'] =  pd.to_numeric(data['Deaths'].str.replace('\W', ''),errors='coerce').fillna(0).astype(int)
data['Recoveries'] =  pd.to_numeric(data['Recoveries'].str.replace('\W', ''),errors='coerce').fillna(0).astype(int)
data['Cases/Deaths'] =  data['Cases']/data['Deaths']


data['Country'] = data['Country'].str.replace(r"\[.*\]","")
In [ ]:
data.drop(data.loc[data['Deaths']==0].index, inplace=True)
